The paper deals with the convergence analysis of algorithms for compressive sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves theoretical analysis of the algorithms, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of restricted isometry property (RIP) condition and iterative thresholding algorithms suggest that it may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. The paper deals with signal processing and optimization, which suggests that it may belong to the signal processing (cs.SP) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves theoretical analysis of algorithms for compressive sensing, which suggests that it may also belong to the statistics (cs.SI) sub-category.
